external_knowledge:
- "most prolific users" refers to users with the highest combined total modifications and accesses; 
- "total modifications" is the sum of all modifications made by a user to different compounds; 
- "access activities" refers to the total number of accesses made by a user; 
- "ranked" implies a descending order, with the highest values first.

- A compound is considered to be in its 'latest version' if it has the highest version number among its versions; 
- 'pchembl value' is a measure of a compound's biological activity; 
- Molecular formula represents the type and number of atoms present in a compound's molecule; 
- 'edit' and 'view' accesses are types of activities users can perform on compounds, indicating whether a user modified a compound or just looked at its information, respectively.

- Biological activity is a measure of how effective a compound is in a particular biological system or process; 
- Molecular weight (mw) is the total number of protons and neutrons in the atoms of a molecule, and it is used as an indicator of the size of the molecule; 
- Partition coefficient (logp) is a measure of the distribution of a compound between two immiscible liquids, such as water and octanol, and it is used as an indicator of the lipophilicity of the compound; 
- Number of heavy atoms (heavy_atoms_counts) is the number of atoms in a molecule that are not hydrogen or helium, and it is used as an indicator of the complexity of the molecule.
